text: Sela pri Kamniku () is a small settlement in the Municipality of Kamnik in the Upper Carniola region of Slovenia. ==Church== The parish church, dedicated to Saint Agnes, was first mentioned in documents from 1232 and was Romanesque in its origins, although it has been frequently rebuilt and expanded, most recently in 1860.Official site of The Roman Catholic Church in Slovenia ==Trivia== In August 2019, an tall wooden effigy of Donald Trump appeared in the village. The sculpture was relocated to Moravče in December 2019 and destroyed in an arson attack in January 2020. ==References== ==External links== * *Sela pri Kamniku at Geopedia Category:Populated places in the Municipality of Kamnik
title: Sela pri Kamniku
